//stpes to create express-application generator

$ npm install express-generator -g
$ express --view=pug myapp
$ cd myapp
$ npm install

//On MacOS or Linux
$ DEBUG=myapp:* npm start
it creates following directory structure and runs the http://localhost:3000

├── app.js
├── bin
│   └── www
├── package.json
├── public
│   ├── images
│   ├── javascripts
│   └── stylesheets
│       └── style.css
├── routes
│   ├── index.js
│   └── users.js
└── views
    ├── error.pug
    ├── index.pug
    └── layout.pug
